This is a simple request and usefull to pause a game, only change this on advanceTime method of Juggler:

if (numObjects == 0) return;  ->   if (numObjects == 0 || _pause) return;

Best regards!

Hello
It seems like a Juggler bug in advanceTime function:
1. mObjects = [null, tween]
On next advanceTime in "for (i=0; i<numObjects; ++i)" loop:
2. i = 0: because of null object at index [0] currentIndex will not been incremented: currentIndex = 0
3. i = 1: tween has been removed from its advanceTime function: mObjects = [null, null]. currentIndex is not equal to i and tween will be moved to index [0] in "mObjects[currentIndex] = object;". So mObjects = [tween, null]

To fix it:

<pre><code>// shift objects into empty slots along the way
if (currentIndex != i && mObjects[i] != null) 
{
    mObjects[currentIndex] = object;
    mObjects[i] = null;
}
</code></pre>

```
public function get root():DisplayObject
